    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on the ValidationResults from the 2024-Q3 experimental campaign, which demonstrated Pearson r = 0.91 and GCI of 4.2% for the hemolysis QoI. Monte Carlo UQ confirmed the P95 hemolysis index remains below the clinical threshold. The team noted that the ValidationResults were generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-2024-q3-build-2 (modelVersion: 2024-q3-build-2), while the UnitOfAssurance records currentModelVersion: 2026-q1-build-7. This version drift was acknowledged but deemed acceptable by the team on the basis that the mesh topology and hemolysis correlation form were unchanged — an assessment that constitutes the W-AR-04 weakness embedded in this synthetic package.",
